# Flight Delay Analysis with Bokeh

This project uses the [Bokeh](https://bokeh.org) library to analyze and visualize flight delay data interactively. It provides insights through histograms, summary tables, and route-specific delay visualizations.

## 📁 Project Structure
'''
- flights.py: Main script to launch the Bokeh server app
- hist.py: Generates histograms of flight delays per airline
- route.py: Visualizes delays based on origin and destination
- table.py: Displays a statistical summary in a table
- flights.csv: Raw flight delay data
- flights_map.csv: (Optional) Additional mapping data'''
## 📦 Requirements

Install dependencies using:
'''
pip install bokeh pandas numpy'''
🚀 Running the App
To launch the application, run:
'''
bokeh serve --show flights.py'''
This will start a Bokeh server and open your browser with the interactive dashboard.

📊 Features
Histogram Panel: Visualize the distribution of arrival delays for selected airlines.
Route Panel: Compare delays by route and airline.
Summary Table: View descriptive statistics of arrival delays for each airline.

